fields.bio: Charlotte started her international racing career in the Asia Powerboat Championships, and has competed in all of our events. This year Charlotte moved into offshore racing with team mate Glynn Norval. Together they achieved third in their debut Cowes-Poole-Cowes race and Charlotte was the first lady across the line in her first Cowes week race. Charlotte plans to build on her successes so far in the next racing seasons. She is a rising talent in powerboat racing, and definitely one to watch.

Starting his racing career in the Rib F3 Championship, Andy became the RYA National Championship winner in 2000 and 2001. It was in 2006 he started racing in Powerboat P1 World Championship and came third overall in his first race. Whilst racing a 19ft Phantom, he was runner up in the E1500 Championship in 2010. As a part of Team Typhoo in the P1 Superstock Championship, he raced a P1 Panther and achieved 2nd overall in 2012.

Barry Culver has been racing since 2002 as both a driver and a navigator after originally getting his adrenaline fix from water skiing. He has travelled the world to race in different classes, including XCAT in Dubai and Offshore Class 3C in Italy. The highlight of his career was in 2016 when he won the 3A UIM World Championship in Norway.

Brian Pelham returned to powerboat racing a few years ago after living and working in Spain. It all paid off for the hard charging racer in 2018 when he won the UKOPRA Class 3N championship with his son Thomas. Brian is new to single seater racing, however, if he can harness his offshore determination on the circuit, the truckie from Surrey will be one to watch.
